Class Move

  • java.lang.Object
    • helpers.Move

  • public final class Move
extends java.lang.Object

    • Constructor Summary

      Constructors 
      Constructor and Description
      Move(java.lang.String s)
      Creates a new Move based on a string with (x1,y1), (x2,y2), ID of the captured piece (0 if nothing captured), whether or not the piece moving was queened (isQueened), whether or not the move was a castle (isCastle), and whether or not the move was white or black (true=white, false=black)

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Concrete Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      int getCaptureID()
      Gives the ID of the piece that was captured in the move (the piece at x2,y2 before the move) If no piece was captured, the ID is 0
      int getX1()
      Gives the starting row of the piece moving
      int getX2()
      Gives the ending row of the piece moving
      int getY1()
      Gives the starting column of the piece moving
      int getY2()
      Gives the ending column of the piece moving
      boolean isCastle()
      Tells whether the move involved castling
      boolean isEnPassant()
      Tells whether the move involved an En Passant
      boolean isQueened()
      Tells whether the move involved queening a piece
      boolean isWhite()
      Tells whether the color of the piece moving was white or black
      java.lang.String toString()
      Gives the readout to that can be outputted to a log file with the string that is broken down in the constructor
